content: I'm brass now? 😳 Just collecting discords, realised I wasn't here.
I just want to stay away from football :pain:
All I have heard this past few days is "It's coming home"
Yeah, then I would get some peace and quiet
And this is why I dislike the whole thing. We just don't care, and we it's all we hear
And when we say we don't care we get "fuck youuuu"
I don't mind people celebrating it, and I guess it's understandable that it's all I hear. It just pisses me off that I am expected to care, and I'm venting
I realise he's blocked me so he can't hear me, but Kenetor's right

Said I didn't care earlier today, someone implied I should be beaten up

So lovely and nice

Apparently much of eastern Europe celebrates it on the 7th of January, and as a legacy from the Soviet era where Christmas was banned there's also a lot of celebrations on new years (someone actually there, correct me if I'm wrong)
